      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That \"make a difference\" stuff just feels like a coping mechanism to ignore the truth. Every piece of data shows we're past the point of no return. It's not about \"small actions\" anymore, it's about the fact that the foundation is gone. It feels lying to yourself to keep trying to build something on a collapsing cliff. It's just exhausting to keep pretending there's a future to prepare for.",
