    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you saying I should take care of my \"mental health,\" but that feels like trying to fix a broken dam with a Band-Aid. Even if I feel \"better\" tomorrow, the reality doesn't change. The world is still going to burn. It doesn't feel like a mental health issue, it feels like a logical response to an impossible situation. If you saw a house was about to collapse, wouldn't you just want to get out before it crushed you? There's no point in staying to watch the end.",
